  }{\f1 \fs20 \b \cf1 *208}{\f1 \fs20 \cf1  Galileo, informed by the work of fellow astronomical realist }{\*\bkmkstart Document1zzSDUNumber94}\f1 \fs20 {\*\bkmkend Document1zzSDUNumber94}{\f1 \fs20 \cf1 Copernicus, }{\*\bkmkstart Document1zzFN_B289}\f1 \fs20 {\*\bkmkend Document1zzFN_B289}{\f1 \fs20 \cf1 }{\field {\*\fldinst {HYPERLINK \\l Document1zzFN_F289 }}{\fldrslt {\f1 \fs20 \ul \cf2 [FN289]}}}{\f1 \fs20 \cf1  was interested in exploring and studying elements of our planet and the celestial bodies whirling "above" it for hard-to-see clues into the reality of celestial dynamics.  Mathematics and a telescope both provided critical lenses through which he could get a better view. }{\*\bkmkstart Document1zzFN_B290}\f1 \fs20 {\*\bkmkend Document1zzFN_B290}{\f1 \fs20 \cf1 }{\field {\*\fldinst {HYPERLINK \\l Document1zzFN_F290 }}{\fldrslt {\f1 \fs20 \ul \cf2 [FN290]}}}{\f1 \fs20 \cf1 }\par 
