\pard \qj \fi0 \li0 \ri0 {\f1 \fs20 \cf1     My research has led me to the conviction that two utterly different approaches to the world have maintained themselves for thousands of years. These approaches include profoundly different social relations, views about the nature of the world, and characteristic thought processes.  Each of these orientations--the Western and the Eastern--is a self-reinforcing, homeostatic }{\*\bkmkstart Document1zzSDUNumber136}\f1 \fs20 {\*\bkmkend Document1zzSDUNumber136}{\f1 \fs20 \cf1 system.  The social practices promote the worldviews; the worldviews dictate the appropriate thought processes; and the thought processes both justify the worldviews and support the social practices.}\par 
