}{\*\bkmkstart Document1zzFN_F285}\f1 \fs20 {\*\bkmkend Document1zzFN_F285}{\f1 \fs20 \cf1 }{\field {\*\fldinst {HYPERLINK \\l Document1zzFN_B285 }}{\fldrslt {\f1 \fs20 \ul \cf2 [FN285]}}}{\f1 \fs20 \cf1 . In 1611, Galileo described his research methodology this way: }\par 
\pard \qj \fi0 \li0 \ri0 {\f1 \fs20 \cf1   Over a period of two years now, I have tested my instrument (or rather dozens of my instruments) by hundreds and thousands of experiments involving thousands and thousands of objects, near and far, large and small, bright and dark; hence I do not see how it can enter the mind of anyone that I have simple-mindedly remained deceived in my observations. }\par 
